Serialized Form

  • Package edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgmnt_4

    • Class edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgmnt_4.Animal extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • master

          Owner master
          This is the owner of the Animal. Since every animal in our system has an owner, It is kept in the superclass, rather than writing one for each of the subclasses.

        • name

          String name
          This is the name of the animal. We keep the name so that we can keep track of the animal, and can use it's name to search for specific animals.

        • age

          int age
          We keep the age of the animal, so that we can reference any disorders or diseases that can affect the animal during certain years of its life.

        • illness

          Disease[] illness
          This array will keep track of any diseases that the animal has, or had during its lifetime..

        • apps

          Appointment[] apps
          This array will hold all the appointments that the animal has at our hospital.

        • animalType

          String animalType
          This String will keep track of the subclass that is made. If a Dog is made, then the animalType will be Dog, if it's a Bird, then the animalType will be Bird and if a Fish, the animalType will be Fish.

    • Class edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgmnt_4.Appointment extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • date

          String date
          This String will keep track of the date of the appointment. It will be set up in the year/month/day fashion.

        • time

          String time
          This String will keep track of the time of the appointment. It will be set up in the ##:##am/pm fashion.

        • client

          Animal client
          This is the Animal that the appointment is for. We keep track of the animal rather than the owner, since an owner could possibly have more than one animal.

    • Class edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgmnt_4.Owner extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          String name
          This represents the name of the Owner. We will need to know the name of each pet owner so that we can return the pet to them when their appointment has been resolved. Without a name, we wouldn't be able to keep track of who owns which pet.

        • address

          String address
          This is the location where the owner lives. We keep their address so that we can contact them at their house if need be. We will keep the address as houseNumber streetName, city, state, zipCode.

        • phoneNumber

          String phoneNumber
          This is the phone number that we can contact the owner through. It is written as a string because we are going to keep it in the form ###) ###-####.
